The paper deals with object categorization, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Multiple Kernel Learning (MKL) framework for learning an optimal combination of descriptors, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of benchmark datasets, which suggests that it involves experimental evaluation, and hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Second Order Cone Programs (SOCP), which is a mathematical optimization technique, indicating that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a relevant sub-category.
